Now back to CP Removal Detection. All actions go after Loop CP Rows, before Get CP File For Archive:
Action 1: Select (Data Operations)

From — fx: body('Read_CP_Excel')?['value']
Switch to text mode
Map — fx: item()?['Control Procedure ID']
Rename to: Extract CP IDs From Excel

Action 2: Dataverse → List rows

Table: Control Procedures
Filter rows — fx: 'pei_emslifecyclestatus eq 890920000'
Rename to: List Active CPs

Action 3: Apply to each

Select output — fx: outputs('List_Active_CPs')?['body/value']
Rename to: Check CP Removals

Inside Check CP Removals:
Action 4: Condition

Left — fx: contains(body('Extract_CP_IDs_From_Excel'), items('Check_CP_Removals')?['pei_controlprocedureidentifier'])
Operator: is equal to
Right — fx: false
Rename to: CP Not In File

Inside CP Not In File → If Yes:
Action 5: Dataverse → Update a row

Table: Control Procedures
Row ID — fx: items('Check_CP_Removals')?['pei_controlprocedureid']
EMS Lifecycle Status: pick Removed from dropdown
Rename to: Mark CP Removed

Action 6: Dataverse → Add a new row

Table: Staged Records
Name — fx: items('Check_CP_Removals')?['pei_controlprocedureidentifier']
Entity Type: Control Procedure (dropdown)
Display Title — fx: items('Check_CP_Removals')?['pei_controlproceduretitle']
What Changed: Removed from Archer (dropdown)
Impact on Evidence: type text → Control Procedure removed from Archer. Existing evidence retained. Future collection will stop.
Import Cycle — fx: concat('pei_importcycles(', variables('varImportCycleID'), ')')
Rename to: Stage Removed CP

Action 7: Increment variable

Name: varCPRemoved
Value: 1

Build all 7 and say "done".


APP Removal Detection — all actions go after Loop App Rows, before Get App File For Archive:
Action 1: Select (Data Operations)

From — fx: body('Read_App_Excel')?['value']
Switch to text mode
Map — fx: item()?['Display Name']
Rename to: Extract App Names From Excel

Action 2: Dataverse → List rows

Table: Applications
Filter rows — fx: 'pei_emslifecyclestatus eq 890920000 and pei_displayname ne ''Enterprise'''
Rename to: List Active Apps

Action 3: Apply to each

Select output — fx: outputs('List_Active_Apps')?['body/value']
Rename to: Check App Removals

Inside Check App Removals:
Action 4: Condition

Left — fx: contains(body('Extract_App_Names_From_Excel'), items('Check_App_Removals')?['pei_displayname'])
Operator: is equal to
Right — fx: false
Rename to: App Not In File

Inside App Not In File → If Yes:
Action 5: Dataverse → Update a row

Table: Applications
Row ID — fx: items('Check_App_Removals')?['pei_applicationid']
EMS Lifecycle Status: pick Removed from dropdown (or Decommissioned if that's a separate value — check your choice. If the choice only has Active/Removed, use Removed)
Rename to: Mark App Decommissioned

Action 6: Dataverse → Add a new row

Table: Staged Records
Name — fx: items('Check_App_Removals')?['pei_displayname']
Entity Type: Application (dropdown)
Display Title — fx: items('Check_App_Removals')?['pei_displayname']
What Changed: Decommissioned (dropdown)
Impact on Evidence: type text → Application no longer in LeanIX export. Existing evidence retained. Future collection will stop.
Import Cycle — fx: concat('pei_importcycles(', variables('varImportCycleID'), ')')
Rename to: Stage Decommissioned App

Action 7: Increment variable

Name: varAppDecom
Value: 1

Build both CP (7 actions) and App (7 actions) and say "done".
